x-sap-shortText: API to query and manage Onboarding process and integrations.

x-servers.description: OData APIs for the SuccessFactors Data Centers

info.title: Onboarding
info.description:
Use these APIs to manage onboarding activities for candidates. Actionable onboarding participants can select office equipment, set goals and arrange meetings for candidates before being hired.

 You can find your company's API server in [List of API Servers in SAP SuccessFactors.](https://help.sap.com/viewer/d599f15995d348a1b45ba5603e2aba9b/LATEST/en-US/af2b8d5437494b12be88fe374eba75b6.html)

externalDocs.description: Onboarding APIs on SAP Help Portal

innererror.description: The structure of this object is service-specific

SFOData.ONB2RehireCheckParams.title: ONB2RehireCheckParams
SFOData.ONB2RehireCheckParams.description:
Rehire Check Params complex type.  
Complex type to hold the rehire params which determines if the user is rehire or not.

SFOData.ONB2OnboardeeDetails.title: ONB2OnboardeeDetails
SFOData.ONB2OnboardeeDetails.description:
Onboardee Details complex type.  
Complex type to hold the information of Onboardee to be created.

SFOData.ONB2ExternalHRISHiringUpdate.title: ONB2ExternalHRISHiringUpdate
SFOData.ONB2ExternalHRISHiringUpdate.description:
Complex type of the External HRIS Hiring Update  
Complex type represents the employee's details in the External HRIS system for whom the update is to be made.

post.summary: After an external user record is created and Employee Central data is added to the record, you can use this funtion import to initiate onboarding process from an external Application Tracking System. It modifies the ONB2Process and ONB2ProcessTrigger MDF objects. All Employee Central entities (PerPerson, EmpJob, EmpEmployment) should be upserted prior to this call.

message.value: Requested entity could not be found.

post.summary: This function import enables you to create an onboarding external user record in the system with information collected from your external Applicant Tracking System (ATS). It also enables you to perform preliminary checks to understand if the onboardee is a new hire or a rehire and take actions as necessary.
